Armstrong Bakam, Bauchi The investigative panel set up by the Bauchi State Government to verify workers without Bank Verification Numbers said it has so far cleared 4,654 civil servants in the state. The PUNCH reported that the state government said it had identified over 41,448 persons on the government payroll without BVN. The Bauchi State Governor, Bala Mohammed, subsequently set up a 17-member panel to unravel the circumstances surrounding the situation. Speaking with journalists in Bauchi, the chairman of the committee, Senator Adamu Gumba, said the committe had recommended to the state government to pay the cleared persons their outstanding October salaries. Copyright PUNCH.
